defs.docs: Keyboard mapping utility for `wayland-client` using libxkbcommon.

attributes.value: / Keyboard mapping utility for `wayland-client` using libxkbcommon.
/ This library provides a simple wrapper for the wayland Keyboard objects,
/ handling all keymap issues using libxkbcommon in a dynamic way (loading the
/ library dynamically and thus not being linked to it).
/ To use it, simply call `MappedKeyboard::new(..)` to wrap you keyboard object
/ and set the key_action callback. This callback will be provided the keycode,
/ the new state of the key (up or down), the keyboard ID,
/ as well as a `KbState` handle.
/ This handle will allow you to retrive the keysym associated to the keycode
/ and compare it to the values defined in the `keysyms` module, or directly
/ restrieve an (utf8) String representation of this character.
allow(non_upper_case_globals)

defs.name: as_symbol
defs.docs: Tries to match this key event as a key symbol according to current keyboard state.

attributes.value: / Tries to match this key event as a key symbol according to current keyboard state.
/ Returns 0 if not possible (meaning that this keycode maps to more than one key symbol).

defs.name: MappedKeyboard
defs.docs: A wayland keyboard mapped to its keymap

attributes.value: / A wayland keyboard mapped to its keymap
/ It wraps an event iterator on this keyboard, catching the Keymap, Key, and Modifiers
/ events of the keyboard to handle them using libxkbcommon. All other events are directly
/ forwarded.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a mapped keyboard by extracting the keyboard from a seat.

attributes.value: / Creates a mapped keyboard by extracting the keyboard from a seat.
/ Make sure the initialization phase of the keyboard is finished
/ (with `Display::sync_roundtrip()` for example), otherwise the
/ keymap won't be available.
/ Will return Err() if `libxkbcommon.so` is not available or the
/ keyboard had no associated keymap.
